                                    <p style=3D"margin: 28px 0 10px;">
                                        Hi there,
                                    </p>

                                    <p style=3D"margin: 28px 0 10px;">
                                        We=E2=80=99re updating how GitHub u=
ses data to improve AI-powered coding tools. From April 24 onward, your int=
eractions with GitHub Copilot=E2=80=94including inputs, outputs, code snipp=
ets, and associated context=E2=80=94may be used to train and enhance AI mod=
els <strong style=3D"color: #0d1117; font-weight: 500;">unless you opt out<=
/strong>.
                                    </p>

                                    <p style=3D"margin: 28px 0 10px;">
                                        If you previously opted out of the =
setting allowing GitHub to collect this data for product improvements, your=
 preference has been retained=E2=80=94 your choice is preserved, and your d=
ata will not be used for training unless you opt in.
                                    </p>

                                    <p style=3D"margin: 28px 0 10px;">
                                        This approach aligns with establish=
ed industry practices and will enable our models to deliver more context-aw=
are AI coding assistance. We have tested this with Microsoft interaction da=
ta and have seen meaningful improvements, including increased acceptance ra=
tes in multiple languages.
                                    </p>

                                    <p style=3D"margin: 28px 0 10px;">
                                        Please review your settings and cho=
ose whether your interactions with Copilot can be leveraged for training AI=
 models before this update goes into effect on April 24. To opt out or adju=
st your settings:
                                    </p>

                                    <p style=3D"margin: 28px 0 10px;">
